      • insertRoot

        private void insertRoot(BinarySearchTree.Node h,
                        int newKey,
                        int newValue)
        Recursive method for insertion a new root. Firstly the recirsion go down to the node (newKey, newValue), after get up by means of rotations, which to bring up this node. Uses the methods rotationToRight() and rotationToLeft(). Used by the method addNew().
        Parameters:
        h - old root of the tree(sub-tree)
        newKey - a new key of a new root
        newValue - a new value of a new root
        See Also:
        addNewRoot(int, int), rotationToLeft(int), rotationToRight(int)

      • rotationToRight

        private void rotationToRight(int key)
        Rotation make the old node is right sub-tree of new root (old left sub-tree of old root).. Usually applies for the left sub-nodes. The old root leaves to down to right.
        Parameters:
        key - whose node must be turn up to right / leaves to down to right.
        See Also:
        insertRoot(workwithtrees.BinarySearchTree.Node, int, int)

      • rotationToLeft

        public void rotationToLeft(int key)
        Rotation make the old node is left sub-tree of new root (old right sub-tree of old root). Usually applies for the right sub-nodes. The old root leaves to down to left.
        Parameters:
        key - whose node must be turn up to left / leaves to down to left.
        See Also:
        insertRoot(workwithtrees.BinarySearchTree.Node, int, int)

        private void fillPir(BinarySearchTree.Node node,
                     int level,
                     java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.StringBuilder> pyramid,
                     boolean keys)
        Fills a pyramid from node for the tree. A pyramid contains key and value of the nodes in String type for each level of the Binary Tree. Uses the methods node.toString, BinaryTree.depth
        Parameters:
        node - from which the pyramid will be filled
        level - of the pyramid, from which the method will fill the pyramid
        pyramid - which will filled by key and value of the nodes in String type of the Binary Tree
        keys - if true, then String type of the nod will contained a key
        See Also:

                       boolean keys)

        Parameters:
